From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keith Calvelli <keith@calvelli.dev>
Date: Thu, 27 Mar 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 19/19] feat: add cross-channel awareness to Telegram context
 prefix

Sid on Telegram didn't know its own email channel was active because
the context prefix only said "you are responding via Telegram" with no
mention of other channels.  Expand the prefix so the LLM knows about
all connected channels.
---
 src/channels/telegram.rs | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/channels/telegram.rs b/src/channels/telegram.rs
index f07b657..c3a8b91 100644
--- a/src/channels/telegram.rs
+++ b/src/channels/telegram.rs
@@ -3,7 +3,9 @@ use super::traits::{Channel, ChannelMessage, SendMessage};
 /// Context prefix prepended to every Telegram message before it reaches the LLM.
 const TELEGRAM_STYLE_PREFIX: &str = "\
 [context: you are responding via Telegram. \
-Keep responses concise. Telegram supports markdown formatting.]\n";
+Keep responses concise. Telegram supports markdown formatting. \
+You also have email (genxbot@calvelli.us via IMAP IDLE) and XMPP channels active. \
+Your email channel receives mail instantly — you can reference recent emails if relevant.]\n";

 use crate::config::{Config, StreamMode};
 use crate::security::pairing::PairingGuard;
--
